# Module Boundaries

## Invariant

Cross-module communication uses **facades only** (`module_*/api.py`). Enforce with `make lint-imports`.

## Allowed dependencies

| Module | May import |
|--------|------------|
| `module-platform` | `cortex-core`, `cortex-models`, `module-*.api` |
| `module-documents` | `cortex-core`, `cortex-models` |
| `module-chat` | `cortex-core`, `module-ai.api` |
| `module-sync` | `cortex-core`, `cortex-models` |
| `module-dms-sync` | `cortex-core`, `cortex-models`, `cortex-connectors`, `module-documents.api` |
| `module-ingestion` | `cortex-core`, `cortex-models`, `cortex-connectors`, `module-documents.api` |
| `module-ai` | `cortex-core` (SearchPort read) |

## Patterns

```python
# BAD — internal import from another module
from module_ai.agents.rag.rag_agent import RagAgent

# GOOD — facade only
from module_ai.api import AiModule
```

```python
# BAD — worker mutates Document.status directly
doc.status = DocumentStatus.READY.value

# GOOD — lifecycle via DocumentsModule
documents.mark_ready(document_id, db, page_count=10)
```

```python
# BAD — dms-sync imports ingestion module
from module_ingestion.tasks import ingest_document

# GOOD — Celery task constants
from cortex_core.messaging.tasks import TASK_INGEST_DOCUMENT, QUEUE_INGESTION
celery_app.send_task(TASK_INGEST_DOCUMENT, args=[doc_id, job_id], queue=QUEUE_INGESTION)
```

## Celery task constants

Always use `cortex_core.messaging.tasks` — never hardcode task name strings.

## Checklist

1. Which module owns the domain? (`feature-placement.md`)
2. New port in `cortex-core` or adapter in `cortex-connectors`?
3. Cross-module call via new `api.py` method?
4. Update import-linter contract in root `pyproject.toml`
5. Run `make lint-imports`

